Root Project

ROOT is a family communication application designed to connect families globally, with features especially suited for seniors, allowing them to stay in touch and share updates with ease.

View Prototype View Promo Video
{/* 설명 섹션 */}

Idea & Interaction Framework

The ROOT project was conceptualized for seniors to help them feel connected with family members, overcoming physical and geographical limitations.

Persona

Persona 01

Judy, 75, feels isolated since the pandemic. She enjoys taking photos but struggles to use smartphone applications due to the time difference with her family in Japan and Seattle.

Persona 02

Jason, 85, lives in Vancouver with four children across different time zones. He hopes for a simple way to send morning greetings to each child.

Storyboard

In this storyboard, Judy sends a scheduled morning message to her daughter, ensuring she won’t disturb her at night.
